---
// ai-plugin-specscore (CLI Skills) — Brazilian Portuguese translation.
// Canonical URL: specscore.md/pt-br/ai/cli-skills/
// Product names (SpecScore, Claude Code, SpecStudio Skills, ai-plugin-specscore) stay English.
// Slash-command names and terminal content stay English.
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../../../../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooterPtBr from '../../../../components/SiteFooterPtBr.astro';
import QsTabsScript from '../../../../components/QsTabsScript.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="pt-BR"
  title="CLI Skills — SpecScore CLI dentro do Claude Code"
  description="Plugin leve do Claude Code que envolve o SpecScore CLI. Expõe specscore lint, feature, task e change-status como comandos nativos do plugin."
  canonical="https://specscore.md/pt-br/ai/cli-skills/"
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main>
    {/* ── Hero ── */}
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="hero__inner">
        <h1 id="hero-title" class="hero__headline">
          O SpecScore CLI, dentro do Claude Code.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero__sub">
          <code>ai-plugin-specscore</code> é um plugin leve do Claude Code que
          envolve o
          <a class="xref" href="/pt-br/cli/">SpecScore CLI</a> open-source.
          Expõe <code>specscore lint</code>, <code>specscore feature</code>,
          <code>specscore task</code> e <code>specscore change-status</code>
          como comandos nativos do plugin — sem escape de shell, sem troca de
          contexto.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__install" id="install">
          <div class="qs-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Método de instalação">
            <button type="button" role="tab" id="qs-tab-claude" aria-controls="qs-panel-claude" aria-selected="true" tabindex="0" class="qs-tab is-active" data-tab="claude">Claude Code</button>
            <button type="button" role="tab" id="qs-tab-setup" aria-controls="qs-panel-setup" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1" class="qs-tab" data-tab="setup">Outros agentes de IA</button>
            <button type="button" role="tab" id="qs-tab-manual" aria-controls="qs-panel-manual" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1" class="qs-tab" data-tab="manual">Manual</button>
          </div>

          <div id="qs-panel-claude" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="qs-tab-claude" class="qs-panel is-active" data-panel="claude">
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin marketplace add specscore/ai-marketplace
<span class="prompt">$</span> /plugin install cli-skills@specscore</pre>
          </div>
          <div id="qs-panel-setup" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="qs-tab-setup" class="qs-panel" data-panel="setup" hidden>
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> specscore agent setup &lt;nome-do-agente&gt;</pre>
            <p class="qs-note">
              Escreve o arquivo de instruções certo para o seu agente —
              <code>claude</code>, <code>copilot</code>, <code>cursor</code>, <code>codex</code>,
              <code>antigravity.google</code>, <code>pi.dev</code> ou <code>opencode</code>.
              Execute dentro de um projeto gerenciado pelo SpecScore. Requer a
              <a class="xref" href="/pt-br/cli/">SpecScore CLI</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div id="qs-panel-manual" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="qs-tab-manual" class="qs-panel" data-panel="manual" hidden>
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> git clone https://github.com/specscore/ai-plugin-specscore
<span class="prompt">$</span> cp -r ai-plugin-specscore/skills /caminho/para/seu/agente/skills/</pre>
            <p class="qs-note">
              Clone o repositório do plugin e copie o diretório <code>skills/</code>
              para onde seu agente carrega os arquivos de skills.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <p class="prose-p">
          Isto é um <strong>wrapper fino</strong> sobre o SpecScore CLI
          para uso dentro do seu agente de IA — nada mais. Sem opiniões
          sobre workflow, sem orquestração de ciclo de vida, sem pipeline
          de slash commands.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-p">
          Se você quer o workflow opinado de spec-driven development —
          <code>/ideate</code>, <code>/specify</code>, <code>/plan</code>,
          <code>/implement</code> — instale o
          <a class="xref" href="/pt-br/ai/specstudio-skills/">SpecStudio Skills</a>.
          Ambos são construídos sobre o mesmo SpecScore CLI.
        </p>

        <div class="callout">
          <strong>Quando usar qual:</strong>
          <ul class="callout-list">
            <li><strong>CLI Skills</strong> — você já conhece o SpecScore e quer o CLI cru no seu loop de agente.</li>
            <li><strong>SpecStudio Skills</strong> — você é novo no SpecScore e quer um workflow guiado.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Comandos ── */}
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="commands-title">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <h2 id="commands-title" class="section-title">Comandos</h2>

        <div class="cmd-block">
          <h3 class="cmd-name">/specscore-lint</h3>
          <p class="cmd-desc">Faz lint de uma árvore de especificações ou arquivo individual. Reporta pass/fail por regra.</p>
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /specscore-lint spec/features/password-reset/
<span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  Feature: password-reset
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  has title, status, and description
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  requirements have acceptance criteria
  <span class="mark-pass">PASS</span>  all AC IDs are unique</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
          <h3 class="cmd-name">/specscore-feature</h3>
          <p class="cmd-desc">Lista, inspeciona ou cria o esqueleto de features do SpecScore.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
          <h3 class="cmd-name">/specscore-task</h3>
          <p class="cmd-desc">Lê e alimenta o quadro de tarefas do projeto.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
          <h3 class="cmd-name">/specscore-change-status</h3>
          <p class="cmd-desc">Transiciona um Feature ou Idea pelo seu ciclo de vida.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Para construtores de ferramentas ── */}
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="builders-title">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
        <h2 id="builders-title" class="section-title">Para construtores de ferramentas</h2>
        <p class="prose-p">
          <code>ai-plugin-specscore</code> existe para que qualquer pessoa
          construindo seu próprio plugin de workflow sobre o SpecScore possa
          depender da superfície do CLI sem reimplementá-la. Se você está
          escrevendo uma alternativa comunitária ao SpecStudio Skills, esse é
          o seu substrato.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-p">
          O código-fonte está em
          <a class="xref" href="https://github.com/specscore/ai-plugin-specscore">specscore/ai-plugin-specscore</a>
          — licença MIT, gratuito para sempre.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  {/* ── Footer ── */}
  <SiteFooterPtBr />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ── */
  .hero {
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
    background: var(--cream);
  }
  .hero__inner {
    max-width: var(--max-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
    animation: fade-in 600ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1) both 180ms;
  }
  .hero__headline {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .hero__sub {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .hero__sub code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .hero__install { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }

  @keyframes fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  /* ── Sections ── */
  .section-title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .prose-p {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .prose-p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .prose-p code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ── Callout ── */
  .callout {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .callout-list {
    margin: var(--space-1) 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .callout-list li { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }

  /* ── Command blocks ── */
  .cmd-block {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .cmd-block:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .cmd-name {
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  .cmd-desc {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
</style>

<QsTabsScript />
